# Build context exclusions — applies to every target in the Dockerfile.
#
# There used to be a second Dockerfile.full.dockerignore. Docker only honours a
# per-Dockerfile ignore file under BuildKit; the classic builder silently falls
# back to this file. Since this file used to exclude external_methods/ and
# Codes_Matlab/, a non-BuildKit build produced an image with no working methods
# and no warning. One Dockerfile, one ignore file, no divergence.
#
# NOT excluded, deliberately: EvaluationData/, Codes_Matlab/ and
# external_methods/ total ~42 MB and are required for methods to run. They are
# baked in so the image needs no host setup.

# Version control and CI
.git/
.github/

# Python environments and caches
venv/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
src/*.egg-info/

# Benchmark results: exclude everything except the pre-computed demo run.
# The demo run is baked in so `docker run` (no compose) shows data immediately.
# Compose users get data from the bind-mounted host outputs/ (cloned from git).
outputs/*
!outputs/run_20260719_191247
!outputs/latest.txt
reports/

# Redundant archives — already extracted as sibling folders
external_methods/*.zip

# Docker's own files (the Dockerfile is still read by the builder)
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose.yml

# Editor / tooling / OS
.vscode/
.claude/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
